seal     : Atari's belated 2600 successor wrapped a 6502 around a smart graphics chip called MARIA that could throw far more sprites at the screen with little CPU help — and it kept the old TIA chip inside for full Atari 2600 backward compatibility. Good hardware, undone by arriving years late into Nintendo's era.
